                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/221.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Special
                        Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 9, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Bevan, Tampico, telegraphs that General Peláez, commanding Villa forces Vera
                    Cruz, has renewed demand 50,000 pesos from Penn <pb facs="1119" n="1003"
                        xml:id="pg_1003"/> Mex Fuel Company, American corporation, and upon refusal
                    comply Peláez shut down company’s plant.</p>
                <p>Request Villa instruct General Peláez withdraw demand and cease interfering
                    company affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
